"| [[French Guiana]]\n| style=\"background:#FFED99;\"| 21,769\n| style=\"background:#FFED99;\"| 64.89\n| 11,777\n| 35.11\n|-\n| align=\"left\"| [[R\u00e9union]]\n| style=\"background:#FFED99;\"| 212,081\n| style=\"background:#FFED99;\"| 60.25\n| 139,917\n| 39.75\n|-\n| align=\"left\"| [[Mayotte]]\n| style=\"background:#FFED99;\"| 19,140\n| style=\"background:#FFED99;\"| 57.11\n| 14,374\n| 42.89\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n| colspan=\"5\"|\n|-\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:left;\"| Source: [http://elections.interieur.gouv.fr/presidentielle-2017/ Ministry of the Interior]\n|}\n\n==== Maps ====\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" heights=\"145px\" style=\"float:left;\">\nFile:\u00c9lection pr\u00e9sidentielle de 2017 par d\u00e9partement T2.svg|First-place candidate by department\nFile:EN - 2017 French presidential election - Second round - Majority vote (Metropolitan France, communes).svg|First-place candidate by commune (2012 borders)\nFile:2017 French Presid election - 2nd round.svg|Vote share by department and major city\n</gallery>\n{{clear}}\n\n== Post-election ==\n{{see also|2017 French legislative election}}\nOn 8 May, Macron joined President Hollande on the [[Champs-Elys\u00e9es]] to commemorate the surrender of Germany on the same day in 1945. The official transfer of power took place on 14 May,<ref name=\"live-20170507\">{{cite news|title=En direct, Emmanuel Macron \u00e9lu pr\u00e9sident : \" Je ferai tout pour que les \u00e9lecteurs FN n\u2019aient plus aucune raison de voter pour les extr\u00eames \"|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/election-presidentielle-2017/live/2017/05/07/suivez-la-soiree-electorale-en-direct_5123713_4854003.html|newspaper=Le Monde|date=7 May 2017|accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref> after which Macron nominated his prime minister and government.<ref>{{cite news|title=Investiture, nomination du premier ministre, l\u00e9gislatives\u2026 Le calendrier des prochaines semaines de Macron|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/election-presidentielle-2017/article/2017/05/07/investiture-nomination-du-premier-ministre-legislatives-le-calendrier-des-prochaines-semaines_5123662_4854003.html|newspaper=Le Monde|date=7 May 2017|accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref> The [[2017 French legislative election|legislative elections]] to elect the 15th [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]] were held a month after the presidential election, with two rounds on 11 and 18 June 2017,<ref name=\"legislatives\">{{cite news|author=El\u00e9a Pommiers|title=Comment se d\u00e9roulent les \u00e9lections l\u00e9gislatives|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/les-decodeurs/article/2017/04/26/les-elections-legislatives-comment-ca-marche_5117626_4355770.html|newspaper=Le Monde|date=26 April 2017|accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref> in which En Marche! presented its candidates under the label of La R\u00e9publique En Marche!; a list of the movement's candidates for the legislative elections was published on 11 May.<ref>{{cite news|title=L\u00e9gislatives : En marche ! fera conna\u00eetre d'ici jeudi \u00e0 midi ses 577 candidats|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-actu/2017/05/08/97001-20170508FILWWW00175-legislatives-en-marche-fera-connaitre-jeudi-a-midi-ses-577-candidats.php|newspaper=Le Figaro|date=8 May 2017|accessdate=8 May 2017|url-status = live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170508182036/http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-actu/2017/05/08/97001-20170508FILWWW00175-legislatives-en-marche-fera-connaitre-jeudi-a-midi-ses-577-candidats.php|archivedate= 8 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the second round of the presidential election on 7 May, Macron announced he would be stepping down as president of [[En Marche!]], Le Pen announced that she would undertake a \"profound transformation\" of the [[National Front (France)|National Front]], and M\u00e9lenchon urged his supporters to mobilize in the legislative elections.<ref name=\"live-20170507\"/>\n\n== Campaign accounts ==\nThe campaign accounts of the 11 candidates were submitted by 7 July 2017 and published in August 2017,<ref>{{cite web|title=Version \u00e9lectronique authentifi\u00e9e publi\u00e9e au JO n\u00b0 0180 du 03/08/2017|url=https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/jo_pdf.do?id=JORFTEXT000035356808|publisher=L\u00e9gifrance|date=3 August 2017|accessdate=9 January 2018}}</ref> and were validated and reimbursement announced by the National Commission for Campaign Accounts and Political Financing (CNCCFP) on 13 February 2018.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n! colspan=\"2\"| Candidate\n! 1st round\n! Spending\n! \u20ac/vote\n! Reimbursement\n|-\n| style=\"background:{{En Marche!/meta/color}};\"|\n| data-sort-value=\"Macron, Emmanuel\"| [[Emmanuel Macron]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 24.01%\n| \u20ac16,698,320\n| \u20ac1.93\n| \u20ac10,640,794<ref>{{cite web|title=D\u00e9cision du 21 d\u00e9cembre 2017 relative au compte de campagne de M. Emmanuel MACRON, candidat \u00e0 l'\u00e9lection du Pr\u00e9sident de la R\u00e9publique des 23 avril et 7 mai 2017|url=https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000036593699|publisher=L\u00e9gifrance|date=13 February 2018|accessdate=13 February 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"background:{{National Front (France)/meta/color}};\"|\n| data-sort-value=\"Le Pen, Marine\"| [[Marine Le Pen]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 21.30%\n| \u20ac12,416,567\n| \u20ac1.62\n| \u20ac10,691,775<ref>{{cite web|title=D\u00e9cision du 21 d\u00e9cembre 2017 relative au compte de campagne de Mme Marine LE PEN, candidate \u00e0 l'\u00e9lection du Pr\u00e9sident de la R\u00e9publique des 23 avril et 7 mai 2017|url=https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000036593681|publisher=L\u00e9gifrance|date=13 February 2018|accessdate=13 February 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"background:{{The Republicans (France)/meta/color}};\"|\n| data-sort-value=\"Fillon, Francois\"| [[Fran\u00e7ois Fillon]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 20.01%\n| \u20ac13,784,073\n| \u20ac1.91\n| \u20ac2,067,625<ref>{{cite web|